What you need to know:

The so-called "Project Big Picture" has been labelled a "power grab" by the Premier League's biggest and wealthiest clubsCritics argue that it is taking advantage of the dire financial position of the English Football League (EFL) - which comprises the three divisions directly beneath the top flight -- amid the coronavirus crisis.A powerful alliance of the Premier League, government and supporters groups has warned about selling control over the game to a small band of clubs.